WEBVTT

00:02.583 --> 00:03.924
Dre: Fathers and sons --
 in the animal kingdom,

00:03.924 --> 00:05.756
the roles have always been
 pretty clear.

00:05.756 --> 00:09.840
Fathers are the alpha male --
 strong, fierce, and in charge.

00:09.840 --> 00:14.014
Sons are the beta male --
 cute, cuddly,

00:14.014 --> 00:16.767
and easily
 smacked out of the way.

00:16.767 --> 00:19.600
But we humans are much more
 evolved than that.

00:19.600 --> 00:20.771
Oh!
  We're our sons' teachers.

00:20.771 --> 00:22.693
What? Uh --

00:22.693 --> 00:24.695
[ Laughs ]

00:24.695 --> 00:26.147
Our sons' role model.

00:26.147 --> 00:27.318
[ Gasps ]

00:27.318 --> 00:28.569
Our sons' hero.

00:28.569 --> 00:30.571
Hey, what's going on,
son?

00:30.571 --> 00:33.574
But there comes a time
 in every dad's life

00:33.574 --> 00:37.328
when things begin to change.

00:37.328 --> 00:40.621
In the animal world,
 when the boy starts to man up,

00:40.621 --> 00:42.333
there are two choices.

00:42.333 --> 00:45.876
The son can eat the father,
 or the father can eat the son.

00:45.876 --> 00:47.428
Come on! Uh-huh!

00:47.428 --> 00:49.550
Ah, get that
out of here, boy!

00:49.550 --> 00:51.222
Gonna have to do
better than that, son.

00:51.222 --> 00:52.593
You gonna have to
better than that at my house.

00:52.593 --> 00:54.175
But when it happens
 in our world,

00:54.175 --> 00:56.637
things aren't that simple.

00:56.637 --> 00:58.599
Come on, what you got?
Oh, you coming in the house.

00:58.599 --> 00:59.770
Oh, you coming
in the house.

00:59.770 --> 01:01.232
[ Groans ]

01:01.232 --> 01:02.603
Ow!

01:02.603 --> 01:04.485
Gah!

01:04.485 --> 01:05.856
What?!

01:05.856 --> 01:07.568
Oh! Oh!

01:07.568 --> 01:08.819
Ha!

01:08.819 --> 01:10.070
Oh!

01:10.070 --> 01:12.573
Oh, oh!

01:12.573 --> 01:14.455
Oh!

01:14.455 --> 01:16.997
[ Both grunt ]
  It was at this moment

01:16.997 --> 01:20.961
I knew I had no other choice
 but to eat my son.

01:20.961 --> 01:22.623
Foul.

01:27.628 --> 01:29.420
Oh!
 Oh!

01:29.420 --> 01:31.512
Yes, YouTube Tuesday.
What we watching? Huh?

01:31.512 --> 01:33.384
Dogs dragging their butts
on the ground?

01:33.384 --> 01:35.976
Oh, even better --
your demise as a man.

01:35.976 --> 01:37.848
Oh!
 Oh!

01:37.848 --> 01:39.099
Connor:
This is trending on Twitter.

01:39.099 --> 01:41.061
The real one,
not the black one "Empire" owns.

01:41.061 --> 01:42.353
Oh!
 Oh!

01:42.353 --> 01:43.524
Oh, look at that.

01:43.524 --> 01:45.896
Testes!
 Charlie:
Oh, this is bad.

01:45.896 --> 01:47.488
You can actually
see the moment

01:47.488 --> 01:49.150
when Junior loses all respect
for his father.
 Yeah.

01:49.150 --> 01:50.941
Charlie,
I'm right here.

01:50.941 --> 01:51.942
Oh, I'm sorry, Dre.

01:51.942 --> 01:53.364
I didn't recognize you

01:53.364 --> 01:55.156
without Junior's testicles
in your face.

01:55.156 --> 01:56.367
Oh!
 Oh!

01:56.367 --> 01:57.948
Outstanding.
He's humiliated!

01:57.948 --> 02:00.080
All right, the boy got lucky
and dunked on me once.

02:00.080 --> 02:01.582
All right,
not a big deal.

02:01.582 --> 02:02.793
[ Knock on door ]

02:02.793 --> 02:04.375
Looking for
an Andre Johnson.

02:04.375 --> 02:05.586
Right here.

02:05.586 --> 02:07.248
I have a gift
from Andre Jr.

02:07.248 --> 02:09.008
Oh.
You see that?

02:09.008 --> 02:12.052
Probably apologizing
for posting that video.

02:12.052 --> 02:14.215
"Dear Dad,

02:14.215 --> 02:16.927
I know how much
you like to eat nuts."

02:16.927 --> 02:19.310
[ Laughter ]

02:19.310 --> 02:22.433
Bon appétit.
 That kid is special.

02:22.433 --> 02:24.315
Look, my son
is not special, all right?

02:24.315 --> 02:26.477
He's just going through a phase
right now

02:26.477 --> 02:28.439
where he's trying
to assert himself.

02:28.439 --> 02:30.731
I'm going through the same thing
with my son.

02:30.731 --> 02:32.273
Trying to man up
on me.

02:32.273 --> 02:34.154
Always asking me
for lunch money.

02:34.154 --> 02:35.656
Bugging me
for a mattress.

02:35.656 --> 02:38.779
Vaccines,
shoes that fit, love.

02:41.202 --> 02:42.913
Love is what
he really wants.

02:42.913 --> 02:44.124
Okay,
you know what?

02:44.124 --> 02:45.876
Halloween is coming up.

02:45.876 --> 02:48.839
And I'm gonna show him
who's smarter, stronger,

02:48.839 --> 02:51.382
and the most terrifying.

02:51.382 --> 02:53.384
I am the prank king,
remember?

02:53.384 --> 02:55.386
Come meet your new cousin,
Colton.

02:55.386 --> 02:58.469
Aunt Jill says be very careful
when you hold him, all right?

02:58.469 --> 03:00.180
[ Screaming ]
 [ Laughs ]

03:00.180 --> 03:02.353
You thought
you killed a baby!

03:02.353 --> 03:04.605
Bam!
Oh, we kicked the baby!

03:04.605 --> 03:05.766
Sulu can't be here.

03:05.766 --> 03:07.268
Where's his line
of fire?

03:07.268 --> 03:08.229
Think!

03:08.229 --> 03:09.940
[ Sighs ]
 [ Dre growling ]

03:09.940 --> 03:11.191
[ Screams ]

03:11.191 --> 03:12.943
Chair monster!
Chair monster!

03:12.943 --> 03:14.525
[ Dre laughs ]

03:14.525 --> 03:16.156
You know, all I've got to do
is get inside Junior's head

03:16.156 --> 03:17.778
and terrorize him
a little bit.

03:17.778 --> 03:20.160
And bam!
I'm back on top.

03:20.160 --> 03:21.532
[ Both chuckle ]

03:21.532 --> 03:23.664
Boy, I can't remember
the last time I had nuts.

03:23.664 --> 03:26.086
Uh, that is because
you are deathly allergic.

03:26.086 --> 03:29.290
That's why this office
is nut-free zone.

03:29.290 --> 03:31.382
Unlike Dre's forehead!
 Unlike Dre's forehead!

03:31.382 --> 03:32.833
U-Unlike Dre's forehead!

03:32.833 --> 03:34.465
Damn it,
I was right there.

03:34.465 --> 03:36.096
Hmm.
 Josh: Sorry.

03:36.096 --> 03:38.218
Hmm.
 [ Doorbell rings ]

03:39.260 --> 03:40.841
Hey.
Oh, my.

03:40.841 --> 03:43.724
[ Gasps ]
Happy almost Halloween!

03:43.724 --> 03:44.765
[ Laughs ]

03:44.765 --> 03:46.807
Guess who I am.

03:46.807 --> 03:49.109
I...
 Bee-yoncé.

03:49.109 --> 03:50.521
Beyoncé.

03:50.521 --> 03:51.522
I see.

03:51.522 --> 03:54.275
And are you wearing...?

03:54.275 --> 03:56.116
Oh, no, no, bronzer.
This is not blackface.

03:56.116 --> 03:58.238
You are the second person
to ask me that, though.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.530
[ Chuckles ]
No, it's not blackface.

03:59.530 --> 04:00.781
Good.

04:00.781 --> 04:03.994
So besides you
coming over here

04:03.994 --> 04:05.456
and daring me
to slap you...

04:05.456 --> 04:07.077
[ Both laugh ]

04:07.077 --> 04:08.829
...is there any other reason
you stopped by?
 Yes.

04:08.829 --> 04:11.372
Last Halloween, remember,
got a little hectic, you know,

04:11.372 --> 04:13.584
with all the others
coming into our neighborhood.

04:13.584 --> 04:16.005
So this year,
I thought we just lock it down

04:16.005 --> 04:17.678
and just host
a mischief night.

04:17.678 --> 04:19.300
And what is
mischief night?

04:19.300 --> 04:20.930
Well, it's a slightly
naughty tradition

04:20.930 --> 04:22.182
on the night
before Halloween,

04:22.182 --> 04:24.645
where we encourage teens
and tweens

04:24.645 --> 04:28.649
to blow off a little steam
in a -- a safe, controlled,

04:28.649 --> 04:30.020
and non-urban way.

04:30.020 --> 04:32.022
Ruby:
Excellent idea!

04:32.022 --> 04:33.694
Wait, what?

04:33.694 --> 04:37.608
I just watched a fascinating
documentary about this.

04:37.608 --> 04:41.281
The one night a year
where all crime is legal,

04:41.281 --> 04:44.455
where its citizens
can release all the demons

04:44.455 --> 04:47.207
pent up inside them.
 Uh, Ruby.

04:47.207 --> 04:48.248
Mm.

04:48.248 --> 04:50.290
That's a movie
called "The Purge."

04:50.290 --> 04:52.503
Great name for it,
Rainbow.

04:52.503 --> 04:53.754
Oh, no, it's a --

04:53.754 --> 04:56.837
What's this neighborhood needs
is a good purge.

04:56.837 --> 04:58.379
Cool,
I want to purge.

04:58.379 --> 05:00.220
Mm-hmm.
 I've dreamed
of purging.

05:00.220 --> 05:02.423
Okay, no -- no purging
and no dreaming.

05:02.423 --> 05:03.514
Go back upstairs,

05:03.514 --> 05:05.305
and I will call you
when dinner's ready.

05:05.305 --> 05:06.887
Janine,
just let yourself out.

05:06.887 --> 05:07.888
Oh, oh.
 Yeah.

05:07.888 --> 05:09.189
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
 Yeah.

05:09.189 --> 05:10.601
Yeah, okay.
 Mnh-mnh-mnh.

05:10.601 --> 05:12.062
See, see,
all those rules.

05:12.062 --> 05:13.814
Those kids
are gonna snap.

05:13.814 --> 05:15.486
See,
in my experience,

05:15.486 --> 05:18.068
a little release
works wonders for the community.

05:18.068 --> 05:20.200
The day after
the Watts riots

05:20.200 --> 05:22.202
was the most peaceful day
of the year

05:22.202 --> 05:24.535
because the devil
came out

05:24.535 --> 05:26.997
and freshly looted Kenmores
came in.

05:26.997 --> 05:28.619
Okay.

05:28.619 --> 05:30.541
I -- I'm just not sure
that's right for mischief night.

05:30.541 --> 05:31.582
It's settled then.

05:31.582 --> 05:34.375
Oh.
 A neighborhood purge!

05:37.007 --> 05:37.878
I'm Ruby,
by the way.

05:37.878 --> 05:39.920
Hi. Janine.
Uh...

05:39.920 --> 05:42.092
Can I touch your hair?

05:42.092 --> 05:43.514
Ooh.

05:44.675 --> 05:47.177
Don't do that.

05:47.177 --> 05:49.179
That night,
 I got my first taste

05:49.179 --> 05:52.062
of a world where Junior
 wasn't afraid of me anymore,

05:52.062 --> 05:54.314
and that was not a world
 I wanted to live in.

05:54.314 --> 05:55.776
Hey.

05:55.776 --> 05:58.318
You get that package
I sent you?

05:58.318 --> 05:59.440
Uh-huh.

05:59.440 --> 06:01.692
It was very amusing.

06:01.692 --> 06:02.943
Amusing?

06:02.943 --> 06:04.655
It was hilarious.

06:04.655 --> 06:07.408
And I say that
with no ego.

06:07.408 --> 06:08.829
[ Laughs ]
Get a load of this kid.

06:08.829 --> 06:10.370
Rainbow: Babe, can you get
the salad bowl?

06:10.370 --> 06:11.161
Sure.
 Thank you.

06:12.583 --> 06:15.045
[ Sighs ]

06:15.045 --> 06:18.088
Who put the large bowl
all the way up top?

06:18.088 --> 06:19.379
Oh, is that high?

06:21.051 --> 06:23.714
I can't even tell anymore.

06:23.714 --> 06:25.385
Here you go,
little guy.

06:25.385 --> 06:28.218
[ Rainbow laughs ]
Like a regular Dane Cook.

06:28.218 --> 06:30.140
Yeah,
that's not a compliment, Bow.

06:30.140 --> 06:31.602
We've gone through this,
okay?

06:31.602 --> 06:35.275
I can't believe you like
this new Junior.

06:35.275 --> 06:36.647
It's cute!
 Wow, Mom.

06:36.647 --> 06:38.228
When you smile,

06:38.228 --> 06:41.151
you have these adorable folds
on the side of your mouth.

06:41.151 --> 06:42.653
Hmm.

06:42.653 --> 06:43.784
Crush him.

06:43.784 --> 06:46.116
Already ahead of you.

06:46.116 --> 06:47.908
Plan is in motion.

06:47.908 --> 06:49.450
Junior.

06:49.450 --> 06:52.332
You know that, uh,
that basket you sent was clever.

06:52.332 --> 06:54.795
Yeah.
 You know, but some people
are allergic to nuts,

06:54.795 --> 06:56.587
so you could have really
hurt someone.

06:56.587 --> 06:57.878
[ Laughs ]

06:57.878 --> 07:02.002
A lot of people
are allergic to peanuts.

07:02.002 --> 07:03.544
You could have really
hurt someone.

07:03.544 --> 07:04.545
[ Laughs ]

07:04.545 --> 07:06.677
[ Organ plays ]
 Charlie Telphy.

07:06.677 --> 07:10.100
Beloved father,
middling employee --

07:10.100 --> 07:11.682
killed by nuts.

07:11.682 --> 07:12.933
[ Woman crying ]

07:12.933 --> 07:15.015
Can't believe
this is happening.

07:15.015 --> 07:17.227
Oh, son.
It's not your fault.

07:17.227 --> 07:20.150
Well, yes, it is.

07:20.150 --> 07:22.943
What?
 This is insane.

07:22.943 --> 07:24.485
Look,
you don't get it.

07:24.485 --> 07:26.697
This is between
father and son, okay?

07:26.697 --> 07:29.409
Junior is testing me,
and I must eat him.

07:29.409 --> 07:30.951
So mind your business

07:30.951 --> 07:33.203
because this is
my Sixteen Chapel.

07:34.875 --> 07:38.789
Did you just say
"Sixteen Chapel"?

07:38.789 --> 07:41.922
Bow,
a man has died.

07:41.922 --> 07:44.965
Can I just say
I love what you're doing here?

07:44.965 --> 07:46.887
Oh, thank you,
Zoey.

07:46.887 --> 07:49.510
How much are we paying
for all this?

07:49.510 --> 07:50.721
Nothing.

07:50.721 --> 07:53.684
Josh -- he volunteered
to pay for the whole thing.

07:53.684 --> 07:54.935
[ Gasps ]

07:54.935 --> 07:57.227
I never told Josh
this isn't real.

07:57.227 --> 07:59.980
Oh, my God.
 [ Sobbing, sniffling ]

07:59.980 --> 08:02.563
Why do you always
take the good ones?

08:07.407 --> 08:08.909
Why are you smiling?

08:08.909 --> 08:11.491
You know Charlie's
not really dead, right?

08:11.491 --> 08:12.743
Yeah.

08:12.743 --> 08:14.374
But one day...

08:14.374 --> 08:15.876
Stevens: At this point,
we'd like to invite anyone

08:15.876 --> 08:17.538
to come forward
and pay their respects.
 One day.

08:20.250 --> 08:21.752
Hey, man,
how you doing?

08:21.752 --> 08:23.423
A little emotional.

08:23.423 --> 08:26.797
A lot of people came out
to say goodbye to me.

08:26.797 --> 08:28.468
I don't see my parents,
though.

08:28.468 --> 08:30.551
But in all fairness,
I didn't go to theirs neither.

08:30.551 --> 08:32.511
Ooh, look at that big-booty girl
over there crying.

08:32.511 --> 08:33.683
Where?

08:33.683 --> 08:35.936
Now would be my chance
if I wasn't dead.

08:35.936 --> 08:37.187
[ Chuckles ]

08:37.187 --> 08:38.688
I'm not dead,
right?

08:38.688 --> 08:39.940
Ch--
Shh, shh.

08:39.940 --> 08:41.270
Here come Junior.

08:41.270 --> 08:43.143
Hold your breath.
Hold your breath.

08:49.449 --> 08:51.321
I don't feel
so good.

08:51.321 --> 08:54.655
You know, that's exactly
what Charlie said

08:54.655 --> 08:58.328
before he closed his eyes
forever.

08:58.328 --> 09:00.040
Gonna miss you,
Charlie.

09:00.040 --> 09:02.422
Let's let him
rest in peace, son.

09:02.422 --> 09:04.625
You killed me.

09:04.625 --> 09:07.928
[ Eerie music plays ]

09:07.928 --> 09:09.299
You didn't hear?
 Hear what?

09:09.299 --> 09:11.551
Son,
it's okay.

09:11.551 --> 09:12.673
Let's go.

09:12.673 --> 09:14.554
♪♪

09:14.554 --> 09:17.137
Oh.
 Hi, guys.

09:17.137 --> 09:18.849
Mischief night starts
in five minutes.

09:18.849 --> 09:21.021
I wanted to make sure
you got your reflectors,

09:21.021 --> 09:21.892
your time-out whistles.

09:21.892 --> 09:24.314
Hard pass,
Janine.

09:24.314 --> 09:26.486
Yeah, if they end up
at the top of a clock tower,

09:26.486 --> 09:27.487
don't call me.

09:27.487 --> 09:29.239
I will not call you.

09:29.239 --> 09:31.071
Attention, neighbors!

09:31.071 --> 09:32.903
The purge
has officially begun!

09:32.903 --> 09:34.364
What?

09:34.364 --> 09:37.367
For the next 12 hours,
all crime is legal.

09:37.367 --> 09:38.538
No, I don't --
I don't mean to quibble.

09:38.538 --> 09:39.910
Not crime.

09:39.910 --> 09:41.752
It's just
some mischief.

09:41.752 --> 09:44.915
Your neighborhood thanks you
for you participation.

09:44.915 --> 09:47.507
This is crazy!

09:47.507 --> 09:50.761
♪♪

09:55.886 --> 09:57.137
[ Growling ]

09:57.137 --> 09:58.679
Wait.

09:58.679 --> 10:00.600
Zoey,
do you see that?

10:00.600 --> 10:02.222
Dude,
there's nothing there.

10:02.222 --> 10:06.106
I think you're starting
to lose it.

10:07.567 --> 10:09.690
Ice cold.

10:09.690 --> 10:11.151
Well-played.

10:11.151 --> 10:13.613
Please let me do more.
I love hurting him.

10:13.613 --> 10:15.736
I'm going in.

10:17.407 --> 10:18.498
Hey, son.

10:18.498 --> 10:22.002
Uh, why aren't you outside
purging?

10:22.002 --> 10:24.745
Wasn't really
feeling up for it.

10:24.745 --> 10:25.746
Oh, yeah.

10:25.746 --> 10:27.547
I guess
it would be kind of hard

10:27.547 --> 10:29.379
trying to have some fun
out there

10:29.379 --> 10:32.803
when you that Charlie
will never have fun again.

10:32.803 --> 10:34.965
Eustace, either.

10:34.965 --> 10:36.807
You know, since you took
his father away from him.

10:36.807 --> 10:39.259
Ah, it's okay,
son.

10:39.259 --> 10:41.351
Try to get you some sleep,
little guy.

10:43.764 --> 10:45.315
Sleep tight.

10:45.315 --> 10:47.267
♪♪

10:52.112 --> 10:53.233
[ Laughs ]
We got him.
 Epic.

10:53.233 --> 10:54.654
I haven't seen someone
that scared

10:54.654 --> 10:56.737
since that Asian lady dropped
what I thought was her gun.

10:56.737 --> 10:57.988
Lady, stop.

10:57.988 --> 10:59.659
Don't run.

10:59.659 --> 11:01.621
I don't want to follow you
all the way home, but I will.

11:01.621 --> 11:03.543
Stop.
Stop, girl.

11:03.543 --> 11:06.126
Turns out
it was my gun.

11:06.126 --> 11:09.049
Well, your gun game is shaky,
but your ghost game is on point.

11:09.049 --> 11:10.500
[ Both laugh ]
 Thanks.

11:10.500 --> 11:12.252
But just
to be clear...
 Mm-hmm.

11:12.252 --> 11:13.553
...I'm not really dead,
right?

11:13.553 --> 11:14.554
Uh...

11:14.554 --> 11:15.635
no, Charlie.

11:15.635 --> 11:17.798
You're good.
 [ Chuckles ]

11:17.798 --> 11:19.800
Just double-checking.
[ Sighs ]

11:19.800 --> 11:22.102
I'm having a blast.
Not confused at all.

11:22.102 --> 11:23.894
So glad
I agreed to do this.

11:23.894 --> 11:25.145
Junior:
Hey, Dad?

11:25.145 --> 11:26.516
I was --
 [ Grunts ]

11:26.516 --> 11:28.108
Hey, son,
how are you?

11:28.108 --> 11:30.400
Uh, I think Charlie's ghost
is haunting me.

11:30.400 --> 11:31.521
Hey, hey,
little man.

11:31.521 --> 11:35.575
There's no such thing
as ghosts, okay?

11:35.575 --> 11:37.738
It's -- it's probably just
your guilty conscience.

11:37.738 --> 11:38.869
[ Exhales sharply ]

11:38.869 --> 11:40.280
But you'll get over it.

11:40.280 --> 11:41.701
Thanks, Dad.
 Or not.

11:41.701 --> 11:43.784
Hey, sweet dreams...

11:43.784 --> 11:44.875
killer.

11:44.875 --> 11:46.787
[ Exhales sharply ]

11:49.289 --> 11:50.961
How long
I got to keep doing this?

11:50.961 --> 11:52.382
Until the next part
of my plan,

11:52.382 --> 11:55.295
where I capture his humiliation
on video.

11:55.295 --> 11:57.177
That way,
it's forever.

11:57.177 --> 11:58.548
Just like death.

11:58.548 --> 12:01.842
Which hasn't yet come for me,
just confirming.

12:01.842 --> 12:02.843
Huh?

12:02.843 --> 12:04.014
Not yet.

12:04.014 --> 12:07.227
Not yet or never?

12:07.227 --> 12:08.608
Hey, guys.

12:08.608 --> 12:10.851
I was thinking we could have
our own mischief night

12:10.851 --> 12:12.853
and have breakfast for dinner.

12:12.853 --> 12:14.775
Wha--

12:14.775 --> 12:16.196
What?

12:16.196 --> 12:18.278
"Dear Mom,
we're sleeping under our beds.

12:18.278 --> 12:20.660
Don't check.

12:20.660 --> 12:23.453
Do not go looking for us
in the purge."

12:23.453 --> 12:24.825
Damn it.

12:24.825 --> 12:27.247
[ Rock music plays ]

12:27.247 --> 12:31.211
♪♪

12:31.211 --> 12:34.544
Okay.
I'm a little scared.

12:34.544 --> 12:35.796
Don't be.

12:35.796 --> 12:37.757
I was born
for this.

12:37.757 --> 12:40.220
We're approaching
my destiny.

12:40.220 --> 12:42.973
Yes, yes, citizens!
Good work!

12:42.973 --> 12:45.685
[ Laughs ]
Now I want you to dig deeper.

12:45.685 --> 12:48.098
Has your neighbor been parking
on our your driveway?

12:48.098 --> 12:51.061
Does you husband
spend too much time

12:51.061 --> 12:53.603
watching the neighbor lady swim?

12:53.603 --> 12:56.446
Okay, Ruby, that's a little bit
more than I -- I bargained for.

12:56.446 --> 12:58.738
Is there any way you can help me
shut this down?

12:58.738 --> 12:59.609
Absolutely.
 Okay.

12:59.609 --> 13:00.700
Uh-huh.

13:00.700 --> 13:02.492
Aah!

13:02.492 --> 13:04.955
That's my mailbox!

13:04.955 --> 13:08.829
Did your neighbor ask
to touch your hair?

13:08.829 --> 13:10.170
Yeah!

13:10.170 --> 13:13.123
Tonight,
we settle all scores!

13:13.123 --> 13:14.544
[ Bat clatters ]
 [ Laughs ]

13:14.544 --> 13:16.586
Now take your pound of flesh!

13:16.586 --> 13:20.010
[ Laughs ]
 [ Cheers and applause ]

13:21.681 --> 13:23.133
All right.
Come on, you got this.

13:23.133 --> 13:24.264
This harness
will hold me, right?

13:24.264 --> 13:25.475
Of course, probably.

13:25.475 --> 13:26.847
Oh, hey, Zoey.
 Hey.

13:26.847 --> 13:28.058
Make sure you capture

13:28.058 --> 13:29.850
your brother's humiliated face,
all right?

13:29.850 --> 13:32.352
Got it.
Again, love hurting him.

13:32.352 --> 13:34.484
You know,
you're a great dad.
 All right.

13:34.484 --> 13:37.647
[ Gasps ] I forgot to pick up
Eustace from soccer practice.

13:37.647 --> 13:39.860
[ Animal howls ]

13:39.860 --> 13:41.111
[ Laughter in distance ]

13:41.111 --> 13:42.702
Dad?

13:42.702 --> 13:44.574
You know, I'm sure he's gonna be
all right, Charlie.

13:44.574 --> 13:46.036
Come on,
let's get you into position.

13:46.036 --> 13:47.407
Come on,
hurry up, man.

13:47.407 --> 13:49.119
Don't be nervous, I got this.
Come on.

13:49.119 --> 13:52.452
[ Heavy-metal music playing ]

13:58.718 --> 14:01.261
Oh, I'm-a go steal those roses
to bring to my teacher tomorrow.

14:01.261 --> 14:02.382
[ Chuckles ] Cool.

14:02.382 --> 14:04.554
I'm gonna make those people
homeless.

14:04.554 --> 14:05.765
♪♪

14:05.765 --> 14:08.348
Hey!
You stop that right now!

14:08.348 --> 14:09.890
This purge is over
for you two!

14:09.890 --> 14:11.811
We are going home now!

14:11.811 --> 14:13.183
[ Gasps ] Oh!

14:13.183 --> 14:15.185
Okay.
All right.

14:15.185 --> 14:17.067
Okay.
You have paintball guns.

14:17.067 --> 14:18.778
Well, we have a home
to get to.

14:18.778 --> 14:22.032
We are taking a little
purge time-out, okay?

14:22.032 --> 14:23.033
No, no.

14:23.033 --> 14:24.364
Hey!

14:24.364 --> 14:27.908
We have opted out
of the purge!

14:27.908 --> 14:30.991
I demand safe passage!

14:31.751 --> 14:33.123
Ohh!

14:33.123 --> 14:36.376
[ Distorted ]
This is cashmere!

14:36.376 --> 14:37.417
♪♪

14:37.417 --> 14:39.419
Oh.

14:39.419 --> 14:42.382
You listen here,
you little [bleep]

14:42.382 --> 14:44.464
I am gonna [bleep] slap you
so hard

14:44.464 --> 14:45.765
that your [bleep]

14:45.765 --> 14:48.008
are gonna be bleeding
out of your [bleep] hole.

14:48.008 --> 14:49.509
Give me this!

14:49.509 --> 14:50.770
Get out of here!

14:50.770 --> 14:51.972
Good lord,
Mommy!

14:51.972 --> 14:54.224
Doesn't it feel good
to purge?

14:54.224 --> 14:56.516
It's like...
your skin is dancing.

14:56.516 --> 14:58.148
Okay, I am worried
about you.

14:58.148 --> 14:59.569
Let's go.
Let's go home.

14:59.569 --> 15:01.111
You stay close
to me.
 Can I have the gun?

15:01.111 --> 15:02.282
No, you can't have
the gun.

15:02.282 --> 15:03.283
Can I have
the Molotov?
 No!

15:03.283 --> 15:04.404
Come on,
son.

15:04.404 --> 15:06.196
You can't keep hiding like this,
all right?

15:06.196 --> 15:09.199
You need to be around people --
  living people.

15:09.199 --> 15:11.121
All right?
Let's watch a movie.

15:11.121 --> 15:12.912
What about "Ghost Dad"?

15:12.912 --> 15:14.995
[ Screams ]

15:17.417 --> 15:19.629
[ Groans ]

15:19.629 --> 15:20.961
[ Laughs ]

15:20.961 --> 15:23.213
We got you,
and we got it all on video!

15:23.213 --> 15:25.215
[ Groans ]
 And it's posted.

15:25.215 --> 15:29.469
We got you,
sucker!

15:29.469 --> 15:32.052
Wait,
this was all a prank?

15:32.052 --> 15:33.433
Yep,
and I'm not really dead.

15:33.433 --> 15:35.055
Right?

15:35.055 --> 15:37.607
The prank king has put you
back in your place, little guy.

15:37.607 --> 15:38.898
Now, come on.

15:38.898 --> 15:40.320
Get up
and show me some love.

15:40.320 --> 15:42.022
Ow. I can't.

15:42.022 --> 15:43.403
Come on, boy, quit playing.
Get up, show me some love.
 Ow!

15:43.403 --> 15:45.695
Stop.
My leg really hurts.

15:45.695 --> 15:48.118
Ow.
 What's happening?
What -- why are you kicking him?

15:48.118 --> 15:51.331
He, uh -- he fell down
the stairs.

15:51.331 --> 15:53.073
That doesn't answer
my question.

15:53.073 --> 15:54.074
Oh, it hurts so bad.
 Oh, my God.

15:54.074 --> 15:55.245
Okay, don't move,
sweetheart.

15:55.245 --> 15:56.626
Don't move,
don't move, don't move.

15:56.626 --> 15:58.788
Let me just see.
 Ah!

15:58.788 --> 16:00.670
Oh, God. Okay, you know
what? I think your leg might
be broken, sweetheart.

16:00.670 --> 16:02.212
[ Sighs ]

16:02.212 --> 16:04.544
[ Scoffs ] Sure.
Bow, his leg might be broken.

16:04.544 --> 16:06.176
[ Groans ]

16:06.176 --> 16:07.717
His leg
is definitely broken.

16:07.717 --> 16:08.798
[ Radio chatter ]
 What?

16:08.798 --> 16:10.470
Sweetheart, we'll be
right behind you, okay?

16:10.470 --> 16:11.471
Come on, guys.

16:11.471 --> 16:12.852
Hey, before you --
Can someone --

16:12.852 --> 16:13.893
Someone close the door,
please.

16:13.893 --> 16:14.894
Yeah,
I got you.

16:14.894 --> 16:17.057
They can't hear me
because I'm dead.

16:17.057 --> 16:18.098
[ Door closes ]

16:18.098 --> 16:19.559
Ugh, I knew it.

16:19.559 --> 16:21.691
Dre didn't know
what he was talking about.

16:25.525 --> 16:26.816
As you can see,

16:26.816 --> 16:28.698
he suffered a hairline fracture
to his left ankle

16:28.698 --> 16:30.990
and a spiral fracture
to his right fibula and tibia.

16:30.990 --> 16:33.033
Sorry.
 That's, uh --

16:33.033 --> 16:34.574
that's definitely
from the stairs, huh?

16:34.574 --> 16:35.665
What?

16:35.665 --> 16:37.577
Not, uh,
not pre-existing condition?

16:37.577 --> 16:40.170
I mean, it could be
from when you kicked me.

16:40.170 --> 16:41.961
I didn't --
I didn't --

16:41.961 --> 16:45.585
Mr. Johnson,
can I speak with you outside?

16:45.585 --> 16:47.467
Uh, can't we talk
right here?

16:47.467 --> 16:49.049
Legally,
I need to...

16:49.049 --> 16:50.890
isolate you
from the victim.

16:50.890 --> 16:52.842
Uh...
The vi--

16:53.893 --> 16:55.635
I'm going to jail.

16:55.635 --> 16:56.936
You should.

16:56.936 --> 16:59.229
You're a bad person.
 I --

16:59.229 --> 17:01.601
I just need to get some of
the particulars of the incident.

17:01.601 --> 17:03.233
I'll get
your son's version next.

17:03.233 --> 17:04.814
Oh, you ain't gonna need
to talk to him.

17:04.814 --> 17:06.356
He's just gonna be doubling up
on what you're about to hear.

17:06.356 --> 17:07.607
Which is?

17:07.607 --> 17:10.569
Okay.

17:10.569 --> 17:13.653
It started with a salad bowl
on the high shelf.

17:13.653 --> 17:16.455
They were literally
in my face.

17:16.455 --> 17:18.248
Resting on my forehead.

17:18.248 --> 17:19.459
So I told him
he killed a man.

17:19.459 --> 17:21.121
Eustace never got picked up
from soccer.

17:21.121 --> 17:22.162
Did I want him to fail?
Yes!

17:22.162 --> 17:24.253
Daddy trouts
eat their sons.

17:24.253 --> 17:25.925
A lot of people say
"Sixteen Chapel."

17:25.925 --> 17:28.758
And I was only kicking him
because I thought he was lying.

17:28.758 --> 17:32.842
Well, Mr. Johnson, it's clear
you're not an abusive father.

17:32.842 --> 17:35.595
Mm.
 You're just a short,
petty man.

17:35.595 --> 17:38.228
Yes!
 Your son still has
two broken legs, you know.

17:38.228 --> 17:39.849
Yes.

17:39.849 --> 17:42.272
♪♪

17:42.272 --> 17:45.815
Jack, I was going to drink
this orange juice,

17:45.815 --> 17:48.238
but would you
care for it?

17:48.238 --> 17:50.610
Only if you take
half my bagel --

17:50.610 --> 17:51.691
the bigger half.

17:51.691 --> 17:53.363
Aww, thank you,
brother.

17:53.363 --> 17:56.075
I haven't asked you
in a while, but...

17:56.075 --> 17:57.076
how are you?

17:57.076 --> 17:59.199
You know,
balls and strikes.

17:59.199 --> 18:01.080
Mm-hmm.
 Are you seeing this?

18:01.080 --> 18:04.043
The kids are being...
not themselves.

18:04.043 --> 18:05.415
It's crazy.

18:05.415 --> 18:10.170
It's like your purge
made them better people.

18:10.170 --> 18:12.382
I hate to say this.
[ Chuckles ]

18:12.382 --> 18:14.013
I think
you were right.

18:14.013 --> 18:16.266
The hell I was.
 What?

18:16.266 --> 18:18.638
Turns out they don't have
purge insurance.

18:18.638 --> 18:20.890
You mess
with my mailbox?
 Huh?

18:20.890 --> 18:22.892
It's Mommy's turn
to play!

18:22.892 --> 18:24.144
What?
 [ Laughs ]

18:24.144 --> 18:26.856
No, no, no!
Not my Benz!

18:26.856 --> 18:28.148
Mischief night!

18:28.148 --> 18:29.569
I'm gonna kill you.

18:29.569 --> 18:31.901
Why didn't you stop me,
Rainbow?

18:31.901 --> 18:34.073
You knew
this wasn't a good idea.

18:34.073 --> 18:35.325
♪♪

18:35.325 --> 18:36.576
Such a doormat.

18:36.576 --> 18:40.079
Well, I told you
a bunch of times this was crazy.

18:40.079 --> 18:41.791
I said,
"This is crazy."

18:43.333 --> 18:45.545
[ Sighs ]

18:45.545 --> 18:47.297
Dre:
Hey, buddy.

18:47.297 --> 18:50.550
I know you been out here
a while.

18:50.550 --> 18:52.302
You don't want to come inside
and put on your costume?

18:52.302 --> 18:53.553
I tried.

18:53.553 --> 18:55.385
And I got it over
one cast,

18:55.385 --> 18:57.927
but I couldn't get it over
the other cast.

18:57.927 --> 18:59.259
Son, I...

18:59.259 --> 19:02.182
I just want to say again
that I'm sorry.

19:02.182 --> 19:03.643
Are you,
Dad?

19:03.643 --> 19:06.816
The doctor said my growth plates
are gonna fuse all wrong.

19:06.816 --> 19:08.648
But you're probably happy

19:08.648 --> 19:11.070
because you'll be the only one
able to reach all the bowls.

19:11.070 --> 19:12.942
That's not
what I want.
 Yes, it is.

19:14.404 --> 19:16.656
If you had it your way,
I'd never grow up.

19:16.656 --> 19:19.038
I'd just be your punching bag
for the rest of my life.

19:19.038 --> 19:21.371
No, son.

19:21.371 --> 19:24.123
I love you.

19:24.123 --> 19:25.164
No, you don't.

19:25.164 --> 19:27.747
You're always trying
to keep me down.

19:27.747 --> 19:29.669
Just because
I can do this!

19:29.669 --> 19:31.631
♪♪

19:31.631 --> 19:32.922
Ah!

19:32.922 --> 19:36.216
Oh, WorldStar!

19:36.216 --> 19:37.347
Rainbow: Yes!

19:37.347 --> 19:39.799
Special delivery
of nuts to your face!

19:39.799 --> 19:41.471
Boom shacka-lacka!

19:41.471 --> 19:44.724
Mom, Mom, this is supposed to be
embarrassing for Dad.

19:44.724 --> 19:45.725
Oh, got it.

19:45.725 --> 19:47.807
What is happening
right now?

19:47.807 --> 19:49.269
You've been pranked.

19:49.269 --> 19:51.901
I faked the whole thing --
like a genius.

19:51.901 --> 19:54.774
[ Cheering ]

19:54.774 --> 19:56.075
But how?

19:57.577 --> 20:00.580
Junior: I figured out
Charlie wasn't really a ghost

20:00.580 --> 20:02.452
when I caught him
eating a Luna bar.

20:02.452 --> 20:05.034
♪♪

20:05.034 --> 20:08.248
It was hard figuring out
how to fall down the stairs.

20:08.248 --> 20:10.540
You can learn anything
on the Internet.

20:10.540 --> 20:12.962
Then came Mom's part.

20:12.962 --> 20:15.174
So, I need three EMTs.

20:15.174 --> 20:16.836
Make one of them a woman.
Uh-huh.

20:16.836 --> 20:18.007
I called in favors at work.

20:18.007 --> 20:19.719
I misused hospital resources.

20:19.719 --> 20:21.471
I had to pay people overtime.

20:21.471 --> 20:23.513
Junior:
Mom, this is kind of my moment.

20:23.513 --> 20:25.395
Rainbow:
Okay, okay, sorry.

20:25.395 --> 20:28.107
[ Laughing ]
He's gonna feel like an idiot!

20:28.107 --> 20:29.399
He should, though.

20:29.399 --> 20:31.230
Boy, you made me
wash you.

20:31.230 --> 20:32.772
[ Laughs ]

20:32.772 --> 20:35.154
You got me,
son.

20:35.154 --> 20:36.906
[ Laughs ]
I'm so proud of you, man.

20:36.906 --> 20:38.197
You really got me.

20:38.197 --> 20:40.360
I think the prank prince
has become the prank king.

20:40.360 --> 20:42.121
Oh, let's slow
your roll.

20:42.121 --> 20:43.533
Oh.
 Let's not get crazy.

20:43.533 --> 20:44.994
Come on,
let's go get changed.

20:44.994 --> 20:46.916
[ Sighs ]
That did not go in.

20:50.540 --> 20:53.583
♪♪

20:56.586 --> 20:59.799
So it turns out when your son
 starts to surpass you,

20:59.799 --> 21:02.472
you don't have to fight it
 or lash out.

21:02.472 --> 21:04.804
There is one other option.

21:04.804 --> 21:09.268
You can embrace it, enjoy it,
 and use it to your advantage.

21:09.268 --> 21:11.441
Next year, we're gonna totally
get your mother, right?

21:11.441 --> 21:13.062
Way ahead of you.

21:13.062 --> 21:15.695
A plan is already
in motion.

21:15.695 --> 21:19.989
♪♪
